Product name: 1" precision spinning top "TriStripe Black Copper" EDC made of copper over aluminium. Great gift. Spinning time up to 10min.
Description:
This precision spinning top is turned out of copper over aluminium on metal lathe. It has a ceramic ball contact point.
Dimensions: D=25mm H=30mm
Spinning time up to 10 min.
A spinning top is not just a child’s toy. It is also an adult toy, in the sense that it helps to figure out how it works. Besides, some adults DO play with spinning tops, and some make very elegant ones. A spinning top is remarkable because it tends to defy gravity while it is spinning. If spun fast enough, a spinning top will rise to a vertical position and happily stay there, despite the fact that it will fall over if it stops spinning.
Suppose a top is so perfectly fashioned that its principal rotation axis (spin axis) goes through its center of mass. (The center of mass, also known as the center of gravity, is the balance point of the object.) If we spin this top carefully, so that it remains perfectly upright while spinning (and gravity can't exert a torque on it about its point), it will spin at a steady angular velocity almost indefinitely. Sliding friction between its tip and the floor does slow it gradually. But if the point is very sharp, sliding friction there exerts very little torque on the top about its rotational axis. Because it's unable to exert a torque on the ground, the top can't exchange angular momentum with the earth. It spins on until it slowly gets rid of its angular momentum through sliding friction and air resistance.
In general, the world is not this accomodating. A slight mismatch between the spin axis and the center of mass will guarantee that gravity exerts a torque on the top about its tip. The rapidly spinning top will precess in a direction determined by the torque exerted by its weight. The precession angular velocity is inversely proportional to the spin angular velocity, so that the precession is faster and more pronounced as the top slows down.

Tan Bunny Hand Puppet
This lifelike hand puppet is sure to entertain all ages, from baby to grandma. 
Hand puppets are great for purely creative play, unlike so many other toys on the market. Mine are designed to provide easy, realistic movement.   The head is partially stuffed, so your hand can go all the way to the nose.  All four legs are open, so the puppet can walk, scratch it's ears, rub it's eyes and nose, play peek-a-boo, etc.  The tummy has a little padded piece inside that rests comfortably right in the palm of your hand and gives each of my puppets a nice full shape, without hindering your capability to move the puppet.
My hand puppets are very durable. I started making these in 1981 and frequently hear stories from people who bought them 15-20 years ago, and still have them after many childhood years of use!
This puppet measures about 8 1/2" from the nose to the opening for your hand.  It is constructed with high-quality American made faux fur.

Product name: Corkstone Cork Turntable Mat Custom Spot-mat, Vinyl Lp Record Mat, Audiophile
Description:
Specs:
1.) Total Thickness = 1/4" inch or roughly 6.35 mm
2.) Total Diameter = 11 - 5/8" inch or roughly 29.53 cm 
3.) The mat has 16 cork dots. The dots are designed to be equally placed around the mat giving proper and even support to the grooves!
4.) The mats are produced from "PURE HIGH QUALITY CORK" Not cheap gasket cork. This is the best quality cork we have to offer! 
5.) The spot-mat supports 12", 10", and 7" records! 
6.) Due to the dense cork material, this mat offers the best improvements to bass and treble frequencies! 
7.) Helps absorb unwanted vibrations!
8.) Each Corkstone Mat will have its own characteristics. All of these mats are different from each other but they come from the same source of cork. The pictures are to give you an idea of what to expect. Each Corkstone Mat is unique and special!
Design Purpose
	This cork spot-mat is designed so that the record rests on the dots and leaves a small gap between the record and the actual cork mat base. This design helps absorb unwanted vibrations and boosts the highs and lows of the vinyl. The dots support the grooves of the vinyl, giving it the most support when the stylus comes in contact with the record. A vinyl record is naturally thicker at the center label and the outer groove. (or the lead in) The dots do not come in contact with the thicker parts of the record, the center label or the outer groove, so the vinyl lays level with cork mat.
Maintenance
	Please keep cork mat clean of any dirt and dust. Use a soft bristle brush, like a good new and unused paint brush, to clean/brush it every once in a while.

____________________________________________________________________
We really love good London Blue Topaz... But that's not what this is -- this might even be better and it's called Neptune Garden Topaz. Created in response to some people's fears about the radiation used to create London Blue, this is a clear topaz that has been treated with Titanium on the back of the stone (where it can't be worn off...) and honestly, it throws far better color. Both Blue and Green flash around incessantly. 
This ring is a nice design; three CZ accents set around two 1 ct colored gemstones. A really pretty Sterling Silver ring -- very solid construction. This is one of those rings you'll pass down to your daughter..
Pretty enough to wear out in the evening.
Please notice the thickness of the silver in this mounting.  These are substantial, without being weighty.  I like my stones well protected, and I assume you do too!  At SylvaRocks, this is the way we make our jewelry.  We don't skimp on metal, and our stones are always hand picked.  
This ring just looks great!
____________________________________________________________________
BTW, Since we make this from scratch after you order it, we have a lot of flexibility.  We can also cast this in yellow, white or rose gold, and in any of 10k, 14k, or 18k.  Obviously, these choices will affect the price, but email us and let us know what you're interested in, and we'll give you the best price we can live with.  We enjoy a strong repeat business, and keep it by making good jewelry you'll want to wear at prices that we both can live with.
